PLACEHOLDER — this file must be replaced before Apple Pay will work on this domain.

Apple Pay (surfaced automatically inside Stripe Checkout's "card" payment
method once enabled — see library-checkout-session's createStripeSession,
which intentionally never restricts payment_method_types so the Dashboard's
enabled methods, including Apple/Google Pay, are offered automatically)
requires this exact file to be the real domain-association file Stripe
generates for you:

  Stripe Dashboard -> Settings -> Payment methods -> Apple Pay
  -> Add a new domain -> download the verification file
  -> replace this file's contents with it exactly (binary, do not edit)

This cannot be generated or verified from this environment — it is tied to
your live Stripe account and this domain's DNS. Until replaced, Apple Pay
will not appear as a payment option even though the rest of the checkout
flow works normally with card/Google Pay.
